<subSubSection id="AC8E4B815171181CFF0EFA72EB6B1B9B" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E42B180A5171181CFF0EFA72ECEB1AA7" blockId="74.[151,1437,1517,2012]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185171181CFF0EFA72EE321A4F" bold="true" box="[151,266,1517,1544]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Known from one species, 
<taxonomicName id="239463895171181CFDDFFA71EDD11A4F" baseAuthorityName="E. Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[582,745,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Convexa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wolfi">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185171181CFDDFFA71EDD11A4F" box="[582,745,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Convexa wolfi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from the 
<collectingCountry id="9C83589A5171181CFCFAFA71EB1C1A4F" box="[867,1060,1518,1544]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
; similar to many 
<taxonomicName id="239463895171181CFB74FA71EA601A4F" authorityName="Olliff" authorityYear="1890" box="[1261,1368,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Atyphella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185171181CFB74FA71EA601A4F" box="[1261,1368,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Atyphella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
especially in outline of pronotum, distinguished by its dorsal colouration of orange pronotum and dark brown elytra with pale orange lateral margins, pale apex and pale part of suture; male pronotum wider than width across elytral humeri, hypomeron not strongly adpressed in anterior half; pronotal punctation characteristic, being small, sparse, areas between punctures very smooth and shiny; elytra convex-sided. Aedeagus with ML constricted preapically and apex thus appearing slightly bulbous. Female macropterous, coloured as for male; larva not associated. [Repeated with slight modifications from 
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB5171181CFDDDF959ECFF1AA7" author="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" box="[580,967,1733,1760]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 188" refId="ref114542" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2009) Systematics of Indo-Pacific fireflies with a redefinition of Australasian Atyphella Olliff, Madagascan Photuroluciola Pic, and description of seven new genera from the Luciolinae (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). Zootaxa, 1997, 1 - 188." type="journal article" year="2009">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin (2009: 54)</bibRefCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E42B180A5171181CFF5EF975EB6B1B9B" blockId="74.[151,1437,1517,2012]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
Of the four species from the Solomons having orange or yellow pronotum and dark brown elytra which are pale margined, two, 
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185171181CFE1BF890ED531B6F" box="[386,619,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
Pygat. 
<taxonomicName id="239463895171181CFE4AF891ED531B6F" authorityName="Pic. Nothing" authorityYear="1923" box="[467,619,1806,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pacifica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbatipennis">limbatipennis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185171181CFD3CF890ECB81B6F" box="[677,896,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
Pygat. 
<taxonomicName id="239463895171181CFD6FF891ECB81B6F" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[758,896,1806,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygatyphella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbatifusca">limbatifusca</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
have LO retracted into anterior half of 
<date id="902A3ECA5171181CFAD0F891EA531B6F" box="[1353,1387,1806,1832]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">V7</date>
and posterior area of 
<date id="902A3ECA5171181CFECCF8ADEE4F1B0B" box="[341,375,1842,1868]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">V7</date>
arched, MPP often obliquely truncate, posterior area of T8 venter with curved ridge slightly to one side of middle, and ML of aedeagus with paired lateral teeth (
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB5171181CFCE4F8C9EBFA1B37" author="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" box="[893,1218,1878,1904]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 188" refId="ref114542" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2009) Systematics of Indo-Pacific fireflies with a redefinition of Australasian Atyphella Olliff, Madagascan Photuroluciola Pic, and description of seven new genera from the Luciolinae (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). Zootaxa, 1997, 1 - 188." type="journal article" year="2009">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin 2009</bibRefCitation>
figs 329, 330–340, 342–369, 370–376). 
<taxonomicName id="239463895171181CFE1DF8E5EEDE1BD3" authorityName="Ballantyne in Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2009" box="[388,486,1914,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Convexa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185171181CFE1DF8E5EEDE1BD3" box="[388,486,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Convexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not possess any of those featur 
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185171181CFC10F8E4EBB21BD3" box="[905,1162,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
es. 
<taxonomicName id="239463895171181CFC29F8E5EBB21BD3" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard. McDermott" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[944,1162,1914,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Magnalata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata" status="comb. nov.">Magnalata limbata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185171181CFB0BF8E5EA2C1BD3" bold="true" box="[1170,1300,1914,1940]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDD379635171181CFB0BF8E5EA2C1BD3" box="[1170,1300,1914,1940]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a black MS, posterior area of the hypomeron is not closely adpressed, and the pronotal punctures are close (
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB5171181CFA9DF801EE501B9B" author="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 188" refId="ref114542" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2009) Systematics of Indo-Pacific fireflies with a redefinition of Australasian Atyphella Olliff, Madagascan Photuroluciola Pic, and description of seven new genera from the Luciolinae (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). Zootaxa, 1997, 1 - 188." type="journal article" year="2009">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin 2009: 56</bibRefCitation>
, figs 17, 18, 227, 228, 229, 230, 235, 236, 238, 239, 244, 
<tableCitation id="A9162DB15171181CFC68F85DEB7D1B9B" box="[1009,1093,1986,2012]" captionStart="TABLE 7" captionStartId="51.[151,239,406,430]" captionTargetBox="[166,1376,478,723]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="TABLE 7. Characteristics of Ventrite 7 Light Organ in As. circumdata (Motsch.) (based on pinned males in Prague collection) (Figs 145−147)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/B0EB488251081865FF0EFE09EE811D95" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" tableUuid="B0EB488251081865FF0EFE09EE811D95">Table 7</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
